## ✅ One‑Line Interview Answer

> `eval()` executes a string as JavaScript code, but it is dangerous, slow, and discouraged due to security and performance issues.

***

## ✅ 10‑Second Interview Explanation

> `eval()` allows dynamic execution of JavaScript code from strings, but it introduces serious security, performance, and maintainability problems, so it should be avoided.

***

